{"title":"Two Poems for T.","author":{"name":"Cesare Pavese translated by Geoffrey Brock"},"publishDate":"2011-06-08","lines":[{"line":"The plants of the lake","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"saw you one morning.","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"The stones the goats the sweat","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"exist outside of days","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"like the water of the lake.","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"The lake remains unmarked","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"by the days’ pain and clamor.","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"The mornings will pass,","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"the anguish will pass,","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"other stones and sweat","stanza":1,"number":10},{"line":"will bite into your blood—","stanza":1,"number":11},{"line":"it won’t always be like this.","stanza":1,"number":12},{"line":"You’ll rediscover something.","stanza":1,"number":13},{"line":"Another morning will come","stanza":1,"number":14},{"line":"when, beyond the clamor,","stanza":1,"number":15},{"line":"you’ll be alone on the lake.","stanza":1,"number":16},{"line":"You also are love.","stanza":2,"number":17},{"line":"Made of blood and earth","stanza":2,"number":18},{"line":"like the others. You walk","stanza":2,"number":19},{"line":"like one who won’t stray far","stanza":2,"number":20},{"line":"from your own front door.","stanza":2,"number":21},{"line":"You watch like one who waits","stanza":2,"number":22},{"line":"and doesn’t see. You are earth","stanza":2,"number":23},{"line":"that aches and keeps silent.","stanza":2,"number":24},{"line":"You have bursts and lapses,","stanza":2,"number":25},{"line":"you have words — you walk","stanza":2,"number":26},{"line":"and wait. Your blood","stanza":2,"number":27},{"line":"is love — that’s all.","stanza":2,"number":28}]}